  "texts": [
    "Caspar first extracts ordered events from acquired app reviews and ranks them using NLP techniques.",
    "Caspar then classifies these events into user actions or application questions, and synthesizes action-question pairs.",
    "Finally, an inference model is trained on the operation-problem pairs.",
    "For a given user action, Caspar can infer possible program problem events, thus enabling developers to understand possible problems in advance to improve program quality.",
    "They experimented with SVM, USE+SVM, and Bi-LSTM networks, respectively; and the results show that the Bi-LSTM model performs better than the other two."
  ],
